A customer’s location must qualify for 24x7 on-site maintenance support which is primarily based on geography.

Please verify that your customer’s location qualifies prior to selling 24x7 on-site maintenance.

For Cisco 24x7 On-site Maintenance (Zip-to-Zone Tool): The customer must be in Zone 1 or Zone 2 in order to qualify for CenturyLink™ IQ Data Bundle Cisco 24x7 on-site maintenance. Please NOTE: mileage constraints may limit Cisco’s ability to meet the 4-hour response target in Zone 2.

For Adtran 24x7 On-site Maintenance: Please send an e-mail to acesCenturyLink@adtran.com with the following information:

Subject: OC 24x7 On-site Location Check

Body: Complete address and telephone number of customer location You will receive an e-mail response indicating that your customer location qualifies or does not qualify for Adtran 24x7 on-site maintenance. Multiple locations can be verified in one e-mail.

NOTE: 24x7 is not available with WAN Optimization.

column8: Internet Port provides Customer Locations with connectivity to the Internet.  Private Ports provides WAN connectivity between Customer Locations.  Customers have the option to allocate traffic to point-to-point Layer 2 connections or Layer 3 MPLS.  Enhanced Ports provides all of the functionality of both an Internet Port and a Private Port in a consolidated communications solution.

Flat billing includes fixed rate for use of full port. Tiered billing includes adjustable bandwidth increments.  Precise Burstable is usage based billing calculated via 95th percentile method.  Data Transfer is usage-based billing calculated via true bit metering.

Card Diversity allows Customer to connect to a secondary card on the same POP as the primary card. Device Diversity allows Customer to connect to a secondary device (Gateway or Router) within the same POP as the primary device.  POP Diversity provides a diversely routed circuit terminating in a physically separate CenturyLink POP than the primary CenturyLink IQ Networking Connection/Port.  Primary reflects the initial port for which a secondary port is diverse from.

The CenturyLink IQ Networking Transition Program addresses three components that will assist customers in migration:

1) MRC/NRC waiver for loop and port—offsets the costs associated with transitioning.

2) Professional Project Management (PPM)— assists with the resources/skill set needed to migrate while minimizing risk and managing uncertainty.

3) Termination liability waiver—removes the CenturyLink QCC contract barrier for existing Frame, ATM and Private Routed Network (PRN).

Centurylink IQ Fiber to the Customer promotion offers customers large bandwidth connectivity at increasing price discounts on ELA Access for IQ Networking with streamlined implementation for Locations in the 14-state in-region, in-franchise territory that are situated along fiber to the node (FTTN) and cell site (FTTC) routes.

 

Fiber to the Customer requires that the Local Loop Speed equal Port Bandwidth.

New Customers or Existing Customers ordering additional locations or renewing services with a Renewal Attachment, toCenturyLink IQ Data Bundle, Data Bundle Pro, Managed Data Bundle, Managed VoIP Bundle, SIP Trunk IAD Bundle orIntegrated Access Package will be eligible to get a Discount on the In-Region (QC) Loop Component.
EFM allows for Special Construction up to 5280 feet without going to CNDC from nearest fiber splice point with RBOC fiber footprint within a ethernet disclosed serving wire center.

New Customers or Existing Customers ordering additional locations or renewing services with a Renewal Attachment, toCenturyLink IQ Data Bundle, Data Bundle Pro, Managed Data Bundle, Managed VoIP Bundle, SIP Trunk IAD Bundle orIntegrated Access Package will be eligible to get a Discount on the In-Region (QC) Loop Component.
